## Summary

**Changed:** `src/prompt_retry.rs` — the `tool_recovery_hint` function, `read_file` hints at both attempt levels.

**What changed:**
• **Attempt 1** (line 151-155): The generic "Use list_files to verify the path, or search for the file" is now a concrete diagnostic: explains the path doesn't exist, then gives a copy-pasteable command template (`rg --files | grep <name>`) plus the `list_files` parent-directory fallback.
• **Attempt 2** (line 108-112): The old "Try bash instead: use `cat <path>`" is now an escalated strategy: first find the exact path with `rg --files`, then read with `cat`/`head`, plus a symbol-based alternative (`rg -n '<symbol>' src/`) for when the agent doesn't know the filename.

**Verification:**
• `cargo fmt -- --check` ✅
• `cargo test prompt_retry` — 84 passed, 0 failed ✅
• `cargo test -- tool_wrappers` — 94 passed, 0 failed ✅
• `cargo check` ✅
• Git diff confirms only `src/prompt_retry.rs` was touched (within task Edit Surface)

**Why it matters:** The old hints were suggestions of tools to try. The new hints are copy-pasteable command patterns that the agent can immediately adapt — converting "check if the path exists" into an action with high probability of finding the right path on the first retry.

